					<p>During a Brainspotting session, your therapist guides you to find eye positions that connect to your emotional or physical experience. While maintaining this eye position, you're supported in processing what comes up - whether that's memories, emotions, or body sensations. This allows your brain to work through trauma at a deep, subcortical level.</p>
